  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>A bad DNS route could be cached to your Internet Service Provider (ISP) and may cause connectivity issues between your payment device and RepairQ. To resolve this issue, try using Google's DNS servers in your network settings.</p><h3 id=\"PAXDeviceTroubleshooting:ChangeYourDNSServers-Windows11-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1934229721\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Payments: Troubleshooting Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295273\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Payment Devices: Changing Your DNS Servers - macOS</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786834\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Payment Devices: Changing Your DNS Servers - macOS Ventura</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786834/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+Windows+10\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786834\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change Your DNS Servers - Windows 10</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295157\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Payment Processing - Start Here!</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PAXDeviceTroubleshooting:ChangeYourDNSServers-Windows11-UpdatingYourConnectionSettingsinWindows11\">Updating Your Connection Settings in Windows 11</h2><p /><p>1. On your computer, navigate to <strong>Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/DNS%20Win%2011%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings page, click <strong>Network &amp; Internet</strong> on the left column.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"226\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/DNS%20Win%2011%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Network &amp; internet status screen, next to your active connection, click <strong>Properties</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/DNS%20Win%2011%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. On the active network screen, look for the DNS Server Assignment selection. Click the <strong>Edit button </strong>next to this option to open the settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/DNS%20Win%2011%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>5. On the Edit network DNS settings popup, update the following fields. When finished with your changes, click <strong>Save</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/DNS%20Win%2011%205.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Automatic (DHCP) or Manual</strong> - Manual</p></li><li><p><strong>IPv4 </strong>- ON</p></li><li><p><strong>Preferred DNS</strong> - 8.8.8.8</p></li><li><p><strong>DNS over HTTPS</strong> - OFF</p></li><li><p><strong>Alternate DNS</strong> - 8.8.4.4</p></li><li><p><strong>DNS over HTTPS</strong> - OFF</p></li><li><p><strong>IPv6 </strong>- OFF</p></li></ul><p /><p>6. When viewing your active network settings, you can see the updated DNS settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"566\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2068807721/DNS%20Win%2011%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
